			  			<h3>Exam Format</h3>
			  			<p>The 37 <b>Exam Format</b> scenarios are similar to the design utilized by the National Board for Certified Counselors (NBCC) for the NCMHCE. These scenarios follow the standard protocol used to identify a mental health disorder for a simulated client case. Many of the scenarios will provide adequate data to make only a single Axis I or II diagnosis; however several will provide data that point to multiple diagnoses.</p>
				  		<p>The Exam Format scenarios will be introduced with a <b>Summary</b> of the client's initial statement or chief complaint. Read each summary carefully.</p>
				  		<p>Note that the scenarios questions become more complex as you advance deeper into the list.</p>
			  		</div>
