		  			</div>
		  			<div class="span4">
		  			<br />
			  			<h3>Answering Questions</h3>
			  			<p>As the counselor, you must then work through appropriate questions and gather the information necessary to formulate a diagnosis and treatment plan.</p>
			  			<p>As you answer each question, note that most have more than one answer that will provide important information. These answers will <b>positively affect your score,</b> so it is best to select as many positive answers as possible. Other answers will not be helpful, and thus will <b>negatively affect your score.</b> Still other answers will be <b>neutral.</b> You will find out the score associated with each answer at the end of the scenario.</p>
			  			<p>Part of the critical thinking evaluation is for you to determine which answers are important. A <b>response</b> is displayed immediately upon choosing an answer.</p>
			  		</div>
		  		</div>
			  
